Consistent quality and service. Food always hot and fast. Employees are always friendly and smiling. The only negative about Raising Cane's is that they don't have more sauces. You either like their signature sauce, honey mustard, or ketchup. However, they make up for it with the consistency of meeting the customers expectations. If you want quick chicken fingers and fries, Cane's is it.

Popped in here because I was starving and it was a better option than McDonald’s. I am very big on customer service so I was pleasantly surprised and it made me happy when I walked in and the young man behind the counter immediately greeted me with, “welcome to Cane’s, how can I help you?” He was a whole mood😊. Even the cooks were smiling!  A lot of times when you walk in to businesses, employees don’t immediately acknowledge you, which is a big no-no if customer service is a priority. I find that it happens usually when I am being served by younger adults.  I should not have been surprised by this young man’s attitude....it’s probably part of Cane’s philosophy. Anyway, my order came fast and my kids’s meal (I’m cutting back, lol) was hot and delicious.

I always considered chicken fingers to be reserved for kids' meals until I ate at Canes. Now I crave them. Their signature sauce is delicious and the box combo with crinkle cut fries, buttered Texas toast, Cole slaw, 4 tenders and a lemonade is pure fast food bliss. The best part tho is that this company hires employee that are consistently so sweet, patient, helpful and genuinely seem happy to be at work...no matter what location I go to. Always a pleasure!

Canes never disappoints when we are in NOLA.   No matter the location! Today we are at the S. Claiborne and it is immaculate. The parking lot is perfectly groomed and well maintained giving it a warm and welcome feeling. The drive thru was packed, but moving at a quick rate. We were greeted immediately at the door. The place smelled ah-mazing! My husband ordered as I went to the restroom. Talk about NICE to walk in and see it was clean. I hate dirty restrooms in a place of business. We ordered the Box and the Caneiac. The chicken was so fresh and hot with a thick, crunchy breading. Fresh and cold cole slaw which I love! So delicious. Everything was top notch quality and quantity.  All of the employees were extremely pleasant. Like genuine, not the “fake forced” because I’m working painted smiles- these folks were smiling and chatting with everyone. That speaks volumes of them and the store. Nice job S. Claiborne!!!

The quality of the people working here needs to be mentioned. The line inside may seem long at times (Mardi Gras) but that's becasue they are moving the call-ahead orders to the side for pick-up to get everyone else through.  Great staff and still upbeat and positive even during parade season.

The chicken fingers here are off the chain. I eat chicken fingers all of the time and can honestly say that these were the best I've ever had. The staff members were very friendly and willing to help my visit very enjoyable. Will definitely be going back.

Got there during rush hour on a VERY rainy evening, the parking lot/shopping center adjacent was jammed with cars and people trying to escape gridlock by the Superdome and the 90/I-10 commute mess...but inside the restaurant it was clean, fully-staffed to get orders out quickly and accurately, and, as far as fast food chicken and the like goes, the taste and quality are FAR better than the cheaper national chains. I bought a meal for my son only and raced home, it smelled so good I wished I had gotten myself some-and I almost NEVER eat fast food...not the cheapest chain, but was satisfied nevertheless.
